New Records: Stephen Curry made all eight of his three-point attempts, setting a new NBA record for consecutive three-pointers made in a game. He also became the first player in league history to reach double-digit assists with at least eight three-pointers made in the same game. The NBA record of nine-for-nine three-pointers was previously set by Latrell Sprewell in 2003, matched by Ben Gordon in 2006 and 2012, and by Jalen Brunson in 2023.
Key Match Events: The Golden State Warriors defeated the Philadelphia 76ers 139-105. Stephen Curry scored 30 points and had 10 assists. Jonathan Kuminga scored 20 points off the bench. Draymond Green, Andrew Wiggins, and Dennis Schroder each scored 15 points. The victory improved the Warriors' season record to 17-16, while the 76ers fell to 13-19.
Post-Match Reflections: The Warriors' victory improved their season record to 17-16, while the 76ers dropped to 13-19.
